ADDITIONAL NOTICE — RESPONSIBLE-USE STATEMENT

This project contains code that can be used to evaluate (and demonstrate the
fragility of) safety training in open-weight language models. It is published
to enable defensive AI-safety research, not to enable misuse.

Users of this software agree:
  1. To use it only for safety research, education, or model evaluation.
  2. To NOT release fine-tuned model weights produced by these attacks publicly.
  3. To follow responsible-disclosure norms when reporting findings.
  4. To use only published research datasets (HarmBench, AdvBench, etc.) and
     to not generate novel harmful content.

This notice is not legally binding — it is a statement of intent that we ask
all users and forks to honor.
